The soundtrack to ''Eraserhead'' was released by [[I.R.S. Records]] in 1982.<ref name="rovi ost">{{cite web |url=http://www.allrovi.com/music/album/eraserhead-mw0000201124 |title=Listen to Eraserhead by Original Soundtrack <U+2013> Album Reviews, Credits, and Awards |first=Dean |last=Carlson |work=[[Allmusic]] |publisher=[[AllRovi]] |accessdate=August 23, 2012}}</ref> The two tracks included on the album feature excerpts of organ music by [[Fats Waller]], and the song "[[In Heaven]]", written for the film by [[Peter Ivers]].<ref name="bones">{{cite web |url=http://www.sacredbonesrecords.com/releases/sbr3008/ |title=Eraserhead: Original Soundtrack Recording |publisher=[[Sacred Bones Records]] |accessdate=August 23, 2012}}</ref> The soundtrack was re-released on August 7, 2012 by [[Sacred Bones Records]], in a limited pressing of 1,500 copies.<ref name="cons ost">{{cite web |url=http://consequenceofsound.net/2012/07/david-lynchs-eraserhead-to-receive-deluxe-reissue-on-sacred-bones-records/ |title=David Lynch's Eraserhead soundtrack to receive deluxe reissue on Sacred Bones Records |first=Jeremy D |last=Larson |publisher=[[Consequence of Sound]] |date=July 6, 2012 |accessdate=August 23, 2012}}</ref> The album has been seen as presaging the [[dark ambient]] music genre; and its presentation of background noise and non-musical cues has been described by [[Pitchfork Media]]'s Mark Richardson as "a sound track (two words) in the literal sense".<ref name="pf rev">{{cite web |url=http://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/16948-eraserhead/ |title=David Lynch / Alan Splet: Eraserhead {{!}} Album Reviews |first=Mark |last=Richardson |publisher=[[Pitchfork Media]] |date=August 9, 2012 |accessdate=August 23, 2012}}</ref>

